{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, a malicious client can give negative feedback about valid content by rejecting it.",
    "DiBenedetto and Papadopoulos (2016) present a clients' reporting system and forwarding policies for the mitigation of CPA in NDN networks.",
    "In the propose scheme, a client can send an extra report about the obtained contents, and then the router uses forwarding strategies known as Evasion Strategies (ES).",
    "ES verifies the content reported if the content is poisoned and avoids its source.",
    "Furthermore, to find the valid contents and their source, the ES is further divided into two strategies: immediate failover and probe first."
  ]
}